# Vercel Web Analytics Configuration - Implementation Report

## Summary
Vercel Web Analytics is **already fully configured** in this Next.js project. No code changes were necessary.

## Current Configuration

### Package Installation
- **Package**: `@vercel/analytics` version `2.0.1`
- **Status**: ✅ Already installed in package.json dependencies
- **Location**: `web/package.json`

### Implementation Details
- **Framework**: Next.js 14.2.18 with App Router and TypeScript
- **Integration File**: `web/app/layout.tsx`
- **Implementation**: Analytics component properly imported and placed according to official Vercel documentation

### Code Implementation
The Analytics component is correctly configured in `app/layout.tsx`:

```typescript
import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";

export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <html lang="pt-br">
      <body>
        {children}
        <Analytics />
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

This implementation follows the exact pattern from the official Vercel Analytics documentation for Next.js App Router projects.

